---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Tom Pickup"
  description="Privacy policy for tompickup.co.uk. How your personal data is handled when you visit this website or contact Tom Pickup."
>
  <section class="legal-page">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: 18 March 2026</p>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <h2>Who I Am</h2>
        <p>
          This website is operated by Tom Pickup, Lancashire County Councillor for Padiham
          and Burnley West. For the purposes of UK data protection law (UK GDPR and the
          Data Protection Act 2018), I am the data controller.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Contact:</strong> <a href="mailto:tom@tompickup.co.uk">tom@tompickup.co.uk</a>
        </p>

        <h2>What Data I Collect</h2>
        <p>This website collects very little personal data:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Contact form:</strong> If you use the contact form, your name, email
            address, and message are composed into a mailto link that opens in your own email
            client. No data is stored on this website's servers.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Email signup:</strong> If you request to join the mailing list, you send
            an email from your own email client. Your email address is then stored in my
            personal email account for the purpose of sending you updates.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Server logs:</strong> This site is hosted on GitHub Pages. GitHub may
            collect standard web server logs (IP address, browser type, pages visited) in
            accordance with their own
            <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy statement</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Lawful Basis for Processing</h2>
        <p>Where personal data is processed, the lawful basis is:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Legitimate interests</strong> (Article 6(1)(f) UK GDPR) for responding
            to your enquiries and carrying out my duties as an elected representative.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Consent</strong> (Article 6(1)(a) UK GDPR) for adding you to the mailing
            list, which you can withdraw at any time by emailing me.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>This website uses the following third-party services:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>GitHub Pages</strong> (hosting) &mdash; Microsoft/GitHub may process server
            log data. See their
            <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy statement</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Fonts</strong> (typography) &mdash; Font files are loaded from
            Google's servers. Google may receive your IP address when fonts are loaded. See
            Google's
            <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This website does not use analytics, advertising, tracking pixels, or social media
          tracking scripts. The share buttons on articles link to third-party services but do
          not load any third-party scripts or set any cookies.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          This website sets minimal cookies. See the <a href="/cookies/">Cookie Policy</a>
          for full details.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Mailing list:</strong> Your email address is retained until you ask to
            be removed.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Correspondence:</strong> Emails sent via the contact form are retained
            for as long as necessary to deal with your enquiry, and may be retained longer
            if related to ongoing casework.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Server logs:</strong> Controlled by GitHub; typically retained for a
            limited period.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access the personal data I hold about you</li>
          <li>Rectify inaccurate data</li>
          <li>Erase your data (where there is no overriding reason to retain it)</li>
          <li>Restrict or object to processing</li>
          <li>Data portability</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent at any time (for mailing list)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, email
          <a href="mailto:tom@tompickup.co.uk">tom@tompickup.co.uk</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>Complaints</h2>
        <p>
          If you are unhappy with how your data has been handled, you have the right to
          lodge a complaint with the
          <a href="https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          ICO helpline: 0303 123 1113<br />
          Website: <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          This policy may be updated from time to time. The date at the top of this page
          shows when it was last revised.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: 7rem 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .legal-page h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .legal-updated {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--separator);
  }

  .legal-content h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-content p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .legal-content ul li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 20px;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .legal-content ul li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 10px;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .legal-content a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .legal-content strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .legal-page {
      padding: 6rem 0 var(--space-xl);
    }
  }
</style>
